node.title: Local hero Barty cruises into third round at Australian Open
node.description: The Australian has powered to a comfortable second-round win over Italian qualifier Lucia Bronzetti.
node.content: ["Ash Barty eased into the third round of the Australian Open with the minimum of fuss on Wednesday, overwhelming Italian qualifier Lucia Bronzetti 6-1 6-1 on Rod Laver Arena.", "The top seed hammered 11 winners to wrap up the first set in 25 minutes and was equally dominant in the second, sealing the victory in under an hour when her opponent netted a backhand.", "Bronzetti, the world No. 142, failed to muster up a single break point over the contes, as the Wimbledon champion lobbed, sliced and pounded her into submission in the bright Melbourne sunshine.", "Barty, hoping to end Australia's 44-year wait for a homegrown women's champion, next faces another Italian in Camila Giorgi with defending champion Naomi Osaka potentially waiting in the fourth round.", "Reuters."]
